reactable example

Código: vignettes/test/reactable.Rmd
reactable.Rmd
data <- MASS::Cars93[
  1:50,
  c("Manufacturer", "Model", "Type", "AirBags", "Price")
]

library(reactable)

reactable(
  data,
  selection = "multiple",
  onClick = "select",
  rowStyle = list(cursor = "pointer"),
  filterable = TRUE,
  highlight = TRUE,
  searchable = TRUE,
  showPageSizeOptions = TRUE,
  striped = TRUE,
  defaultColDef = colDef(vAlign = "center", minWidth = 150),
  paginationType = "jump",
  elementId = "cars",
  columns = list(
    Manufacturer = colDef(
      sticky = "left",
      rowHeader = TRUE,
      name = "",
      cell = function(value) {
        htmltools::strong(value)
      }
    )
  )
)

About rostemplate

Desarrollado por Diego Hernangómez.

About rOpenSpain

rOpenSpain is a community of enthusiasts of R, open data, and reproducibility that comes together and organizes itself to create R packages of the highest quality for the analysis and use of Spanish data of general interest.

"rOpenSci is our form, Spanish public data our matter"

Sitio creado con pkgdown 2.2.0.

Template rostemplate by dieghernan, based on Universal Theme for Hugo.
